Here's the full program:

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("john", 30);

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase
};

Console.WriteLine(JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options));

public record Person(string name, int age);
```

**Output:**
```json
{"Name":"john","Age":30}
```

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase` — introduced in .NET 9. It converts your lowercase constructor parameter names (`name`, `age`) to PascalCase (`Name`, `Age`) in the serialized JSON. No custom policy needed.
